<TITLE> Dhaka-Kuwait direct flights launched </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com)  Kuwait Airways on Friday launched direct flights between Chittagong and Kuwait. The flights will run on Friday and Saturday, promising cheap yet comfortable commute. The Airbus-300 can carry 250 passengers each time, the officials said at a news conference at Peninsula Hotel in the port city. Samiur Razzak, sales manager of the airlines in Bangladesh, said the flights have been introduced to facilitate a considerable number of expatriates who live in Middle East from the greater Chittagong's Cox's Bazaar, Noakhali and Comilla districts, and businessmen. Passengers can travel to 48 destinations, including in Europe and America, he said. From Kuwait, the first flight carrying 232 passengers landed at Chittagong airport at 4:25am. The flight will have 232 economy class and 18 business class seats. b
